      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When a government fails to enforce its own laws, it signals that those laws are optional, which is the very definition of anarchy. If immigration laws are selectively ignored, it creates a dangerous precedent where any law can be disregarded by any group, eroding the foundational concept of legal predictability. This erosion of the rule of law means that domestic laws regarding taxation, contracts, and criminal behavior lose their moral and legal authority, destabilizing the entire social contract.",
      "source": "target",
